                <summary>Abstract</summary>
                <article class="has-text-justified p-2">This paper examined the effect of entrepreneurial orientation on
                    the innovation performance
                    of hospitality industry in Oyo State Nigeria. The study adopted survey research design. Primary
                    data was sourced through structured questionnaire. The study adopted quantitative methods
                    by using survey questionnaire structure in 5-point likert scale. 288 copies of questionnaire were
                    administrated to the managers/owners of Hotels in Oyo state, out of which 272 copies were
                    retrieved for analysis. The result of regression analysis showed an R-square of 0.39 which
                    indicated that 39% of change in innovative performance of firm was accounted for by
                    independent variables. The results also indicated that innovativeness (β = 0.230, t = 3.687,
                    p < 0.05), competitive aggressiveness (β=0 .187, t=3.320, p < 0.05) and motivation (β=0.294,
                        t=5.150, p < 0.05) have positive and significant effect of the innovation performance on
                        hospitality industry in Oyo State. However, both risk taking (β=0.007, t=.110, p> 0.05)
                        and autonomy (β = 0.110, t = 1.793, p > 0.05) have positive but insignificant effect on the
                        innovation performance of hospitality industry in Oyo state. The study further revealed that
                        proactivenss (β = -0.021, t = -0.346 p > 0.05) has insignificant and negative effect on the
                        innovative performance. The study concluded that entrepreneurial orientation affected
                        performance of hospitality industry in Oyo State. It was recommended that; stakeholders in
                        hospitality industry should consider entrepreneurial orientation especially innovativeness,
                        competitive aggressiveness and motivation as strategies to enhance performance in hospitality
                        industry.</article>
